"4:36:4" : {s: 4, a: 36, w: 4, r: "شرك", t: "تُشْرِكُوا۟", l: "أَشْرَكَ", lc: 71, tl: "tush'rikū", lb: "শরীক করা, শিরক করা",e: "associate", b: "তোমরা শিরক করো", i: "kamu mempersekutukan", f: 3, rm: "to be a companion, be sharer/partner. shirkun - share, participation, polytheism, idolatry, making associate/partner with Allah. shariik (pl. shurakaa) - associate, partner, sharer. Nouns of the second declension when followed by the affixed pronouns take the three inflexions thus shurakaa, shurakaai, shurakaaa. shaarak (vb. 3) - to share with. ashraka (vb. 4) - to make a sharer or associate, give companions (e.g. to God), be a polytheist or idolater. ashraktumuuni - you associated me as partner. mushrik - one who gives associate to God, polytheist. mushtarikun (vb. 8) - one who partakes or shares.", ag: "فعل مضارع صيغة ٤ وضمير متصل ", eg: "Verb Imperfect 4th form and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "IMPF", qual: "(IV)", deg: "2", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "JUS", lu: "أَشْرَكَ،شُرَكَآءُ،شُرَكَٰٓؤُا۟،يُشْرِكُ"},
